2 HOUSE BILL 352
1 5–223.
2 (b) (1) There is a Concentration of Poverty School Grant Program in the State.
3 (2) The purpose of the Program is to provide grants to eligible schools with
4 a high concentration of eligible students.
5 (3) The Program consists of the:
6 (i) Personnel grant; and
7 (ii) Per pupil grant.
8 (c) (9) The personnel and per pupil grant may be used [through fiscal year
9 2027] to provide the programs required under COMAR Title 13A, Subtitle 04, including
10 13A.04.16.01.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
12 1, 2026.
